.TH CONV_FLOAT_S32 "9" "2025-05-27" "LinuxCNC Documentation" "HAL Component"
.SH NAME

conv_float_s32 \- Convert a value from float to s32
.SH SYNOPSIS
.HP
.B loadrt conv_float_s32 [count=\fIN\fB|names=\fIname1\fB[,\fIname2...\fB]]
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
\fBconv-float-s32.\fIN\fB\fR (requires a floating-point thread)
Update 'out' based on 'in'
.SH PINS
.TP
.B conv-float-s32.\fIN\fB.in\fR float in \fR
.br
.ns
.TP
.B conv-float-s32.\fIN\fB.out\fR s32 out \fR
.br
.ns
.TP
.B conv-float-s32.\fIN\fB.out-of-range\fR bit out \fR
TRUE when 'in' is not in the range of s32
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.B conv-float-s32.\fIN\fB.clamp\fR bit rw \fR
If TRUE, then clamp to the range of s32.  If FALSE, then allow the value to "wrap around".
